{"id":"quant-ph/0311003","submitter":"Mitsuru Hamada","authors":"Mitsuru Hamada","title":"Notes on the Fidelity of Symplectic Quantum Error-Correcting Codes","comments":"20 pages. Ver.2: typographycal errors corrected","journal-ref":"International Journal of Quantum Information, vol.1, no.4,\n  pp.443--463, 2003","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  Two observations are given on the fidelity of schemes for quantum information\nprocessing. In the first one, we show that the fidelity of a symplectic\n(stabilizer) code, if properly defined, exactly equals the `probability' of the\ncorrectable errors for general quantum channels. The second observation states\nthat for any coding rate below the quantum capacity, exponential convergence of\nthe fidelity of some codes to unity is possible.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 1 Nov 2003 14:25:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 24 Nov 2003 10:29:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
